# Hybrid Cloud Cortex Activation - Walkthrough

## 🎯 Mission Objective
Establish a fully operational Hybrid AI architecture combining local compute (Linux node) with Google Cloud AI services, enabling seamless browser automation and intelligent task execution across the network.

---

## ✅ Phase 1: Browser Agent Activation - COMPLETE

### What Was Built
Created a Python-based browser automation agent using Playwright that connects to a remote Chrome instance running on a Windows machine via Tailscale VPN.

### Key Components
- **Script:** [browser_agent.py](file:///home/gonya/01_Projects/PRJ-004_AI_Agents/02_Dev/browser_agent.py)
- **Test Script:** [test_phase1_chrome.py](file:///home/gonya/01_Projects/PRJ-004_AI_Agents/02_Dev/test_phase1_chrome.py)
- **Target:** Windows Node at `100.127.194.111:9222`
- **Protocol:** Chrome DevTools Protocol (CDP)

### Test Results
```
🔌 Connecting to Chrome at http://100.127.194.111:9222...
✅ Chrome Debugger URL: ws://100.127.194.111:9222/devtools/browser/...
   Browser: HeadlessChrome/124.0.6367.78

🚀 Establishing CDP connection...
✅ CDP Connection established!
✅ New browser context created

🌐 TEST TASK: Navigating to google.com...

============================================================
✅ PHASE 1 SUCCESS!
============================================================
📄 Page Title: Google
🔗 Current URL: https://www.google.com/
============================================================
```

### Technical Achievement
- ✅ Cross-platform automation (Linux → Windows)
- ✅ Network-transparent browser control via Tailscale
- ✅ Foundation for credential extraction and web automation

